Install and Configure Splunk on Kali
-->Objective

   The objective of this lab is to guide students through installing and configuring Splunk Enterprise on an Ubuntu machine. 
   By the end of this task, students will have Splunk running as a service, accessible through the browser, and ready to collect and analyze security logsâ€”an essential skill for SOC analysts.

-->Lab Setup Requirements

   Operating System: kali linux

   Tools Needed: Splunk Enterprise (Free), Terminal

   Privileges: sudo access

-->Steps & Commands Used
  1. Download Splunk
     wget -O splunk-9.3.0-51ccf43db5bd-linux-2.6-amd64.deb "https://download.splunk.com/products/splunk/releases/9.3.0/linux/splunk-9.3.0-51ccf43db5bd-linux-2.6-amd64.deb"

  2. Install Splunk
     sudo dpkg -i splunk-9.3.0-51ccf43db5bd-linux-2.6-amd64.deb

  3. Enable Splunk Service
     cd /opt/splunk/bin
     sudo ./splunk enable boot-start --accept-license
     sudo ./splunk start


     Set an admin username and password when prompted.

  4. Access Splunk Web

     Open browser:

     http://<your-server-ip>:8000


     Log in using the admin credentials you created.

-->WhatI Saw

   Splunk installation through .deb package

   First-time setup and admin configuration

   Splunk service enabled to auto-start

   Accessing Splunk Web UI successfully

